»Yani Neko« von Yuuko Natsuyoshi

Mit einem Visual und Teaser Trailer wurde heute bekannt, dass der Comedy Manga »Yani Neko« von Nyan Nyan Factory eine Anime-Adaption erhält. Die Anime-Adaption startet im Juli 2026 im japanischen TV. Zudem gab man die Mitwirkenden an der Produktion sowie den Sprechercast offiziell bekannt.

»Chainsmoker Cat« entsteht nach Vorlage des Manga von Nyan Nyan Factory, der im Weekly Young Magazine von Kodansha seit Februar 2023 läuft und bislang 10 Bände umfasst. Band 11 erscheint am 6. Februar in Japan. Eine englische Übersetzung ist bei Seven Seas erhältlich. Regie führt Taku Kimura (Star Wars: Visions, Tatooine Rhapsody), das Drehbuch übernimmt Takashi Aoshima (Kakushigoto). Für das Charakterdesign ist Riki Matsuura verantwortlich (Chainsaw Man The Movie: Reze Arc, Devil Design), die Musik steuert Keiichi Suzuki bei (Tokyo Godfathers). Produziert wird die Animation bei Bibury Animation Studios. 

📜 Beschreibung 》
Yani ist eine Catgirl mit einer richtig heftigen Zigarettensucht. Sie raucht so viel, dass ihre Wohnung dauerhaft nach Asche riecht und überall Kippen herumliegen. Dazu kommt noch anderer Müll, sodass ihr Zuhause eher wie ein Chaoslager wirkt als wie ein Ort zum Wohlfühlen. Yani weiß eigentlich, dass es so nicht weitergehen kann, und nimmt sich immer wieder vor, endlich aufzuhören. Doch jedes Mal wird sie nach kurzer Zeit schwach. Das Verlangen trifft sie so hart, dass sie fast sofort wieder zur Zigarette greift. Zwischen Selbstironie, Rückfällen und kleinen Momenten von Einsicht stolpert sie durch den Alltag. Die Geschichte zeigt ihr Leben als überzeichnete, aber irgendwie auch menschliche Sucht Comedy. Die große Frage bleibt, ob Yani es schafft, sich zu ändern oder ob sie für immer als Kettenraucherin, die ihr Leben nicht auf die Reihe kriegt weiterlebt.

Or at the very least being aware of how you interact with it. If the AI is solving the problem for you, you probably aren't learning.

Interestingly, they note that the AI group ran into fewer errors than the non-AI group and often ended up with working code the first time they ran their code. This likely means that the struggle of dealing with issues led to deeper thinking about the problem.

images.alt:
Errors and Trio Skill Not all errors carry the same weight in skill development in our study. Certain errors
require a deeper understanding of the Trio library, which may account for differences in learning outcomes.
Figure 14 shows that the most common errors are not directly related to the Trio library: NameError and
AttributeError are typically typos made on variable names or function names that are quickly corrected.
Other errors are directly related to Trio: RuntimeWarning appears when a coroutine was never awaited and
TypeError appears when a trio function gets a coroutine object instead of an async function. These errors
force an understanding of key concepts on how the trio library handles corountines and the usage of await
keywords that are tested in the evaluation. Although participants in the AI condition also encounter errors
(Figure 15), there are much fewer Trio-related errors encountered.
For participants in the control group, the higher frequency of encountering errors leads to more critical thinking
about what is happening with the code and how to used the new library being presented. Furthermore,
the frequent appearance of errors specifically related to the Trio library ensures that these specific concepts
are gained in the process of completing the task. Together, these two differences suggest that encountering
errors may play a significant role in the formation of coding skills. Moreover, our original motivation for the
importance of preserving debugging skills may hinge on the acquisition of these skills without relying on AI.

The Moltbook Network for AI Agents and the Future of Booking

external.description:
"AI agents are talking to each other on the Moltbook social network — no humans required. Soon, they’ll be booking travel too.

A brand-new and chaotic corner of the internet is offering a preview of what travel distribution might look like when AI agents — not humans — become the primary customers.

Moltbook, a social network launched this week built exclusively for AI agents, has already attracted 1.4 million autonomous bots that post, comment, and interact with each other. Humans can only observe. Former OpenAI research director Andrej Karpathy called it "the most incredible sci-fi takeoff-adjacent thing I have seen recently."

The platform is messy — full of spam and security vulnerabilities — and what Karpathy himself describes as a "dumpster fire." But underneath the chaos is something travel companies and their tech executives should study closely: the first large-scale test of what happens when AI agents form networks"

record.text: Skiing and Climate Change: The Future of Snowmaking

external.description:
"The ski industry is racing to fight the impacts of climate change mainly with snowmaking. But the irony is hard to ignore: the very systems keeping many slopes open also burn energy and emit greenhouse gases.

Aspen One, among the few U.S. ski companies with resorts that opened on time this winter, says snowmaking and glacier covers are only temporary defenses against years of record low snowfall. 

The real challenge, the company argues, is the climate crisis itself.

Rapid global warming and higher temperatures are eroding the foundations of winter tourism, shortening ski seasons, reducing snow and making it less predictable.

"Snowmaking isn’t the core issue; the energy being used is," said Chris Miller, senior vice president of sustainability at Aspen One. "We’re focused on tackling the root causes of climate change, not just adapting within resort boundaries.""

Google Maps is a powerful tool. It can help your business become easier to find and reach for potential customers.

If you run a small local shop, restaurant, grocery store, or service business, you can increase your visibility. You do this by adding your business to Google Maps. It can bring in foot traffic or online inquiries.

In this blog post, we will take you through a step-by-step guide on how to add your business to Google Maps. Let’s get started on the journey to putting your business on the digital map!

* * *

## **What is Google Maps?**

Google Maps is a widely used tool for navigating and exploring the world. It allows users to view satellite imagery, road maps, and 360-degree street views.

But it’s not just for personal use – Google Maps also offers a range of features that can benefit business owners.

Adding your business to Google Maps helps potential customers find your business and its location easily. This can greatly increase your online presence and boost your business growth.

Like FacileWay is ranking in the top 3 locally for the service term of “Best SEO Service”

This key term helps FacileWay attract potential visitors. These visitors are hot customers looking for a local organisation to work with.

If you simply optimize your business profile with key terms of services you offer, you can get some organic customers from Search Engines.

* * *

## **Benefits of Adding Your Business to Google Maps**

With a user base of approximately 154 million people each month, the potential reach is enormous. Here are some key benefits of adding your business to Google Maps:

### **1. Increased visibility**

By appearing on Google Maps, your business will gain greater visibility to potential customers. When users search for products or services related to your business, your address and map location will be displayed, making it easier for them to find and connect with you.

### **2. Greater accessibilit** y

With your business listed on Google Maps, customers can easily access your physical location. They can get directions to your business, ensuring a seamless and convenient experience for both new and existing customers.

### **3. Reach potential customers**

By appearing on Google Maps, you can tap into a vast pool of potential customers who are actively searching for businesses like yours. This can lead to an increase in foot traffic and potentially more sales.

* * *

## **How to Add Your Business on Google Maps**

Setting up your business profile on Google Maps is a simple and effective way to boost your online presence and reach a wider audience.

We have a family business in pharmacy. So I am going to create a business profile for Google Maps for my family business, Fahim Medical Hall. Here is the step-by-step guide-

**Step 1:** Sign in to your Google account or create a new one if you don’t have one already. Having a Google account is necessary to **create a Google My Business account.**

**Step 2:** Go to google.com/business and click on the “Add your business to Google” Option.

**Step 3:** Choose the category that best represents your business from the provided options. This helps potential customers find your business when using the search bar on Google Maps or Google Search.

**Step 4** : If you have a physical location that customers can visit, mark it on the map. If you don’t have a physical location, you can still create a service-area business listing.

**Step 5:** Provide your business contact details, including phone number and website, to make it easy for customers to get in touch.

**Step 6** : Verify your business by selecting the verification option that works best for you.

This can be done through a verification code sent to your business address or an instant verification if you have already verified your website with Google Search Console.

****Final Step:**** Add a cover photo, business hours, and a detailed business description to customise your business profile****.**** Use this space to highlight what sets your business apart.

If your business offers any online delivery. You can also include information about the delivery area that you can cover from your store.

Congratulations! You have successfully created your Google Business Profile and submitted your business on Google Maps.

This is how it will appear on the search engine when you look for your business. Your target audience can easily find your business or store using the directions or by directly calling you.

* * *

## **FAQs Related to Google Business Profile**

Here are some FAQs Related to Google Maps and Business Profile-

### **1. What is a Google Business Profile?**

A Google Business Profile is a free online listing. It provides important information about a business, such as its name, address, phone number, and hours of operation.

### **2. How do I verify my Google Business Profile?**

Google usually verifies a Business Profile by sending a verification PIN through mail, email, or phone. The method depends on your choice.

### **3. Can I change my business category on my Google Business Profile?**

Yes, you can update your business category in your Business Dashboard. It’s essential to choose the most accurate category to ensure your business is properly classified.

### **4. What should I do if I haven’t received my verification PIN for my Google Business Profile?**

If you haven’t received your PIN within the expected timeframe, you can request a new one through the Google Business Profile dashboard.

### **5. Do I need a physical address to create a Google Business Profile?**

Yes, a physical address is generally required for most businesses to create a Google Business Profile. However, there are exceptions for businesses that operate exclusively online.

### **6. How can I improve my business’s visibility on Google Search and Maps?**

Optimising your Google Business Profile by providing accurate business details, posting updates, and actively managing reviews can help improve your visibility on Google Search and Maps.

### **7. What is the Business Dashboard on Google Business Profile?**

The Business Dashboard lets business owners manage and update their information. They can respond to reviews, post updates, and see insights about their profile’s performance.

* * *

## **Final Thoughts**

As you saw, it’s quite easy to add your business to Google Maps. You can get a lot of real customer reviews for your business.

These reviews help businesses build trust and credibility among potential customers. They also influence customers’ purchase decisions. Additionally, they significantly impact search rankings.

When customers see a business with a high number of positive reviews, it instils confidence in the quality of products or services offered.

Positive reviews act as social proof. They show that other customers had a good experience. This builds trust and encourages potential customers to choose your business over competitors.

To encourage positive customer reviews, businesses can share the review request link with customers, making it easy for them to leave their feedback.

You should respond to reviews professionally. Thank customers for positive feedback. Address any concerns in negative reviews. This shows that the business values customer feedback, further enhancing credibility.

But remember one thing, businesses should not solicit fake reviews or write their own. Google has strict guidelines against such practices and can penalise businesses that engage in them.

Additionally, if a business comes across an inappropriate review, it can flag it for Google to take appropriate action.
